test-switch: switch/case dispatch correctness on objtype=riscv64

WHAT IS TESTED
--------------
classify(int v) in main.c is a switch with 9 non-contiguous case values
(1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 21, 34, 55) and a default. Called 14 times from
main(): once per case value (in shuffled order, not declaration order),
plus 5 values chosen to hit "default" from different positions relative
to the case set - below the lowest case, above the highest case, and in
gaps between existing cases. Each call's return value is compared
against a hand-computed expected value and the result is printed over
UART0 as "<label> PASS" or "<label> FAIL".

WHY THIS CONSTRUCT
------------------
Initially picked on the theory that switch might compile to an indirect
jump table, sharing the address-materialization code that already had
two confirmed bugs this session (optab.c's C_LECON routing, and the
missing SB init - see the BinOutput project's memory). Reading
sys/src/cmd/il/swt.c before building this test showed that's not how
this compiler implements switch at all: swit2() lowers it to a binary
search tree of plain compare-and-branch instructions (OEQ/OGT + a
recursive bisection once there are 5 or more cases), not a jump table.
So this test isn't exercising the address-materialization path - it's
exercising the compare-tree codegen and label patching (patch()) across
a function with more branch targets than anything tested so far, plus
default-case fallback from multiple tree positions. Kept as the first
test anyway since it's still new, non-trivial code generation with no
prior coverage.

HOW TO READ THE RESULT
-----------------------
Watch UART0 (same console as the other rv_baremetal-boot-plan9-riscv64-*
examples). Each of the 14 lines should read PASS. A final line reads
either "ALL TESTS PASSED" or "SOME TESTS FAILED (see above)". The commit
LED is a no-terminal fallback: solid on once the test finishes means
all 14 passed; a fast blink means at least one FAIL was printed.

BUILD
-----
mk (produces main.out and main.bin, same convention as the other
rv_baremetal-boot-plan9-riscv64-* folders - main.bin is the flashable
headerless output, built with -s to strip Plan9 symbols).
